  "texts": [
    "In some cases, lay volunteers were even used in the production of misinformation (LIE DETECTOR (Mihalcea and Strapparava 2009), FAKENEWSAMT (Pérez-Rosas et al. 2018)).",
    "The benefit of crowdsourcing is clear; especially at the article level, datasets that use expert annotations (BUZZFEED-WEBIS (Potthast et al. 2018), ALLCOTT & GENTZKOW (Allcott and Gentzkow 2017), FAKENEWSCORPUS (Pathak and Srihari 2019)) tend to be much smaller than those leveraging crowdsourcing.",
    "A common strategy to combat this, is to blend the 'Article' and 'Publisher' level labelling schemes (FAKENEWSNET/GOSSIPCOP (Shu et al. 2019), FAKENEWSCORPUS (Pathak and Srihari 2019), MM-COVID (Li et al. 2020)).",
    "Either factual or misinformation articles are manually verified, and the complementary class is sampled from a set of publishers commonly associated with misinformation or factual articles, respectively.",
    "A similar strategy is to blend the 'Article' and 'Claim' level labelling schemes."
  ],
